-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Aug 18
-- 
-- Mon Aug 18, 2014 02:45AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Aug 18 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Boiko Borisov, leader of centre-right GERB party which is expected to win the early elections in October, said Bulgaria's next government should have at least 10 Muslim Deputy Ministers (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor, Capital daily, 24 Chasa, Duma). -- Professor Steve Hanke, who was advisor to former Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov and architect of the Balkan country's currency board system, recommended bankruptcy for troubled Corporate Commersial Bank (Corpbank) <6C9.BB>, adding that he was not acquainted with the audit reports of the bank (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor, Duma). -- Some 63 refugees, including 18 women and 16 children, have arrived in the Black Sea city of Varna on a ship. Most of them said they were Afghani nationals and a small part of them said they were Syrian citizens (Trud, Standart, Sega, Monitor, Capital daily, Duma, 24 Chasa). -- Bulgaria striker Valeri Bojinov is set to join English Premier League side West Ham United from Levski Sofia (Meridian Match, Standart, Presa, 24 Chasa).